      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Regression testing for LLM applications ensures that improvements to one capability do not silently degrade another. Unlike traditional software where a function either returns the right value or it doesn't, LLM outputs are probabilistic \u2014 regressions are statistical and require an eval suite, a stored baseline, and a comparison pipeline to detect reliably."
          }
        ]
      },
