      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Storing and Loading Baselines"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A baseline is a stored snapshot of scores from a known-good prompt version. Without a stored baseline, you cannot tell whether a change improved or degraded quality \u2014 you only have the current score, not the delta. Store baselines as JSON files committed alongside the prompt version:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, asdict\n\n@dataclass\nclass BaselineSnapshot:\n    prompt_version: str\n    model: str\n    scores: dict[str, float]  # case_id -> score\n    pass_rate: float\n    timestamp: str\n\n    def save(self, path: str):\n        Path(path).write_text(json.dumps(asdict(self), indent=2))\n\n    @classmethod\n    def load(cls, path: str) -> \"BaselineSnapshot\":\n        data = json.loads(Path(path).read_text())\n        return cls(**data)\n\n# Save a new baseline after a confirmed-good prompt version\ndef save_baseline(\n    result: EvalResult,\n    model: str,\n    path: str = \"baselines/current.json\"\n):\n    snap = BaselineSnapshot(\n        prompt_version=result.prompt_version,\n        model=model,\n        scores=result.scores,\n        pass_rate=result.pass_rate,\n        timestamp=\"2026-07-01T00:00:00Z\"  # stamp externally\n    )\n    Path(path).parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n    snap.save(path)\n    return snap"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Regression Gate"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The regression gate is a hard check: any case that previously passed (score \u2265 threshold) and now fails (score < threshold) blocks the change, regardless of overall score improvement. This is stricter than comparing aggregate pass rates \u2014 a 2% average improvement that breaks 3 previously-reliable cases is a net regression."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def regression_gate(\n    baseline: BaselineSnapshot,\n    candidate_scores: dict[str, float],\n    threshold: float = 0.8,\n    canary_ids: set[str] | None = None\n) -> dict:\n    regressions = []\n    canary_failures = []\n\n    for case_id, baseline_score in baseline.scores.items():\n        candidate_score = candidate_scores.get(case_id)\n        if candidate_score is None:\n            continue  # new case, not a regression\n        was_passing = baseline_score >= threshold\n        now_failing = candidate_score < threshold\n        if was_passing and now_failing:\n            entry = {\n                \"case_id\": case_id,\n                \"baseline_score\": baseline_score,\n                \"candidate_score\": candidate_score,\n                \"delta\": candidate_score - baseline_score\n            }\n            regressions.append(entry)\n            if canary_ids and case_id in canary_ids:\n                canary_failures.append(entry)\n\n    overall_baseline = baseline.pass_rate\n    overall_candidate = (\n        sum(1 for s in candidate_scores.values() if s >= threshold)\n        / len(candidate_scores)\n    )\n\n    return {\n        \"passed\": len(regressions) == 0,\n        \"regressions\": regressions,\n        \"canary_failures\": canary_failures,\n        \"overall_delta\": overall_candidate - overall_baseline,\n        \"recommendation\": \"deploy\" if not regressions else \"block\"\n    }"
          }
        ]
      },
