      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Running the Suite in CI"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nfrom anthropic import AsyncAnthropic\n\nasync_client = AsyncAnthropic()\n\nasync def run_case(case: dict, system: str, grader, threshold: float) -> dict:\n    resp = await async_client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-opus-4-8\",\n        max_tokens=512,\n        system=system,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": case[\"input\"]}]\n    )\n    score = grader(resp.content[0].text, case[\"expected\"])\n    return {\"id\": case[\"id\"], \"score\": score, \"passed\": score >= threshold}\n\nasync def run_regression_suite(\n    system_prompt: str,\n    cases: list[dict],\n    grader,\n    threshold: float = 0.8,\n    concurrency: int = 10\n) -> dict[str, float]:\n    semaphore = asyncio.Semaphore(concurrency)\n    async def bounded(case):\n        async with semaphore:\n            return await run_case(case, system_prompt, grader, threshold)\n    results = await asyncio.gather(*[bounded(c) for c in cases])\n    return {r[\"id\"]: r[\"score\"] for r in results}\n\n# In CI: load baseline, run suite, apply gate, exit with code 1 on failure\nimport sys\n\nasync def ci_regression_check(new_prompt: str, baseline_path: str):\n    baseline = BaselineSnapshot.load(baseline_path)\n    candidate_scores = await run_regression_suite(new_prompt, EVAL_CASES, my_grader)\n    gate = regression_gate(baseline, candidate_scores, canary_ids=CANARY_IDS)\n    print(json.dumps(gate, indent=2))\n    if not gate[\"passed\"]:\n        print(f\"REGRESSION: {len(gate['regressions'])} case(s) regressed\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    print(f\"PASS \u2014 delta: {gate['overall_delta']:+.1%}\")\n\nasyncio.run(ci_regression_check(NEW_PROMPT, \"baselines/current.json\"))"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Updating the Baseline"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After a change passes the regression gate and is deployed, update the baseline to the new scores. This locks in the higher quality level \u2014 future changes must now maintain it:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def promote_to_baseline(\n    candidate_scores: dict[str, float],\n    new_prompt_version: str,\n    model: str,\n    baseline_path: str = \"baselines/current.json\",\n    history_dir: str = \"baselines/history/\"\n):\n    # Archive the current baseline before overwriting\n    current = BaselineSnapshot.load(baseline_path)\n    Path(history_dir).mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n    archive_path = f\"{history_dir}{current.prompt_version}.json\"\n    current.save(archive_path)\n\n    # Save new baseline\n    pass_rate = sum(1 for s in candidate_scores.values() if s >= 0.8) / len(candidate_scores)\n    new_baseline = BaselineSnapshot(\n        prompt_version=new_prompt_version,\n        model=model,\n        scores=candidate_scores,\n        pass_rate=pass_rate,\n        timestamp=\"externally-stamped\"\n    )\n    new_baseline.save(baseline_path)\n    print(f\"Baseline promoted: {current.prompt_version} \u2192 {new_prompt_version} ({pass_rate:.1%})\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Archive every superseded baseline, not just the current one. When a regression appears after several iterations, you may need to trace back through baseline history to find which change introduced it. Without history, that trace is impossible."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Detecting Statistical vs. Individual Regressions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM outputs at temperature > 0 are stochastic. A single failing run for a given case may be noise, not a true regression. Two strategies address this:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Run N times per case:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " For stochastic outputs, run each case 3\u20135 times and take the mean score. Gate on mean score drop rather than single-run failure. Expensive but eliminates false positives from sampling variance."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Use temperature 0 for regression runs:"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The simplest approach. Temperature 0 eliminates most sampling variance \u2014 a case that fails at T=0 is very likely a real regression, not noise. Production may use a different temperature, but regression gating at T=0 is sufficient for most tasks."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "async def run_case_n_times(\n    case: dict,\n    system: str,\n    grader,\n    n: int = 3,\n    temperature: float = 0.0\n) -> float:\n    tasks = [\n        async_client.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-opus-4-8\",\n            max_tokens=512,\n            temperature=temperature,\n            system=system,\n            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": case[\"input\"]}]\n        )\n        for _ in range(n)\n    ]\n    responses = await asyncio.gather(*tasks)\n    scores = [grader(r.content[0].text, case[\"expected\"]) for r in responses]\n    return sum(scores) / len(scores)  # mean score over N runs\n\n# Gate on mean score \u2014 eliminates single-run noise\n# Case regresses only if mean score falls below threshold"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Regression Triage: Finding the Root Cause"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When a regression is detected, the blocking output should include enough information to triage the root cause immediately, without re-running the suite:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def regression_report(\n    gate_result: dict,\n    cases: list[dict],\n    baseline_outputs: dict[str, str],\n    candidate_outputs: dict[str, str]\n) -> str:\n    if gate_result[\"passed\"]:\n        return f\"PASS \u2014 overall delta: {gate_result['overall_delta']:+.1%}\"\n\n    lines = [\"REGRESSION DETECTED \u2014 change blocked\", \"\"]\n    case_map = {c[\"id\"]: c for c in cases}\n\n    for r in gate_result[\"regressions\"]:\n        cid = r[\"case_id\"]\n        case = case_map.get(cid, {})\n        lines.append(f\"Case: {cid}\")\n        lines.append(f\"  Input:     {case.get('input', 'N/A')[:80]}\")\n        lines.append(f\"  Expected:  {case.get('expected', 'N/A')[:80]}\")\n        lines.append(f\"  Baseline:  {baseline_outputs.get(cid, 'N/A')[:80]}\")\n        lines.append(f\"  Candidate: {candidate_outputs.get(cid, 'N/A')[:80]}\")\n        lines.append(f\"  Score: {r['baseline_score']:.2f} \u2192 {r['candidate_score']:.2f} ({r['delta']:+.2f})\")\n        lines.append(\"\")\n\n    return \"\\n\".join(lines)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A good regression report shows the input, the expected output, the baseline output (what the previous prompt produced), and the candidate output (what the new prompt produces) side by side. This reduces triage time from minutes of manual re-running to seconds of reading the CI output."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Intentional Regressions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sometimes a change intentionally changes behavior on a previously-passing case \u2014 for example, a case that was passing by producing an incorrect but plausible output, and the new prompt correctly fails it. This is a \"regression\" in the mechanical sense (score dropped) but not in the quality sense."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handle this with an explicit exception list: cases that are allowed to regress in a specific version. Document the reason in the exception list so future reviewers understand why the gate was bypassed:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "REGRESSION_EXCEPTIONS = {\n    # Format: case_id -> reason string\n    \"case_047\": \"v3 intentionally stopped accepting 'yes/no' for ambiguous inputs; case was a false pass.\",\n    \"case_112\": \"Behavior change: model now declines to guess on out-of-scope questions (by design).\"\n}\n\ndef regression_gate_with_exceptions(\n    baseline: BaselineSnapshot,\n    candidate_scores: dict[str, float],\n    threshold: float = 0.8,\n    exceptions: dict[str, str] | None = None\n) -> dict:\n    exceptions = exceptions or {}\n    result = regression_gate(baseline, candidate_scores, threshold)\n    # Remove excepted regressions from the blocking list\n    result[\"regressions\"] = [\n        r for r in result[\"regressions\"]\n        if r[\"case_id\"] not in exceptions\n    ]\n    result[\"excepted\"] = [\n        {\"case_id\": cid, \"reason\": reason}\n        for cid, reason in exceptions.items()\n        if cid in {r[\"case_id\"] for r in result.get(\"regressions\", [])}\n    ]\n    result[\"passed\"] = len(result[\"regressions\"]) == 0\n    result[\"recommendation\"] = \"deploy\" if result[\"passed\"] else \"block\"\n    return result"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run the regression suite on every prompt, model, or parameter change \u2014 not just on new feature work."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Store baselines as versioned JSON snapshots. Compare candidate scores against the stored baseline, not a moving target."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Apply a hard regression gate: any previously-passing case that now fails blocks the change, regardless of aggregate improvement."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Structure the suite into canary (100% threshold, hard block), regression (95%+, soft block), coverage (\u2265 baseline, trend-track), and boundary (informational) categories."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Run the suite in CI with async concurrency. Exit with code 1 on gate failure to block deployment automatically."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "After a successful deployment, promote the candidate scores to the new baseline and archive the old one."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
